                    <death when="0542" syriaca-computed-start="0542-01-01" source="#bib1253-2">542</death>
                    <state type="martyr" source="#bib1253-2">
                        <p>Martyr</p>
                    </state>
                    <note>Fiey provides the following bibliographic citations: <quote source="#bib1253-2">Bedjan, appendice a Jab-Alaha, 347-94.
BHO, 353.
Hoffmann, Ausziige, 78- 86.
Devos, "Martyrs persans", 216.</quote>
                    </note>
                    <note type="abstract" xml:id="abstract-en-1253">Gregory Pīrānguŝnasp was a Zoroastrian
          Convert from the family of Mihran. He was imprisoned by the Byzantines and treated well by
          Justin I. He converted to Christianity. He was freed by a truce with Kusro, but his family
          put him to death in 542.</note>
                    <event type="attestation" xml:id="attestation1253-1" source="#bib1253-2">
